Cloud maturity assessment measures how effectively an organization adopts and manages cloud technologies.

Assessment areas commonly include:

* Governance maturity
* Security maturity
* Operational excellence
* Automation
* Cost optimization
* DevOps adoption
* Skills development

For example, an organization that automates deployments, enforces governance policies, and continuously optimizes costs demonstrates a higher level of cloud maturity than one relying on manual processes.

Regular maturity assessments help organizations identify improvement opportunities and prioritize future cloud investments.
